\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Core of the Greatest Commandment
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Jesus summarized the entire law and the prophets with one foundational truth: Love God with all your heart, soul, mind, and strength, and love your neighbor as yourself.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Being a "doer of the law" simply means having a heart that is inwardly transformed to love God completely.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 When we love God with all our heart, soul, mind, and strength, we learn how to organize our entire lives around the will of God.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We must constantly ask ourselves one vital question about our daily decisions: "Are your choices increasing or decreasing your love and dependency on God?".\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Putting God First (God as Your Aim)
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Putting God on the throne of your life not only honors Him, but it also fulfills your deepest needs, because you were designed to find your greatest delight in God.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 True joy and fulfillment come from recognizing and treasuring God's glory above all else.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 When you make God your primary aim, everything else in your life becomes secondary; it doesn't mean other things are unimportant, it just means they are not the 
\f2\i most
\f1\i0  important.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 If we build our lives on anything other than Jesus and His Word, we are building on shaky ground; loving God means making His Word our firm foundation, source of wisdom, and direction.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 The Motivation for Loving God (He Loved Us First)
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We do not love God to earn our salvation; we love God because He took the "first step" and loved us while we were still His enemies.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 God did not wait for us to get our act together before sacrificing Jesus on the cross; His proactive love is the engine for our love.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 True love for God isn\'92t dutiful, forced action; it is a joyful response rooted deeply in God's grace and forgiveness.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Because we have been freed from the bondage of sin and death, we can now live out of the overflow of God's grace to love and serve Him.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Loving God as "Satisfied Children"
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The very first step of our church's mission is to "Be" \'97 to love God by resting in the Father's love as His satisfied children.\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Loving God means having a heart that is fully devoted to Him\'97not a perfect heart that never makes mistakes, but a heart that longs for God more than anything else.\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 When we fail, a heart that loves God runs back to Him in repentance instead of running away and hiding in shame.\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 To love God is to abide in Him like a branch connected to a vine, recognizing that apart from Him, our lives spiral into chaos and produce nothing lasting.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Loving God Through Joyful Obedience
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Keeping God's commandments is how we abide in His love, and when our hearts are truly transformed, the things of God are no longer burdensome but become a source of joy.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Our obedience to God is not a new set of steps to earn salvation; rather, our obedience is the outward display of a transformational change in our hearts.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Loving God means living as a "living sacrifice," which simply means daily living under the authority and direction of Jesus as your spiritual act of worship.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The most satisfying life you can ever imagine is one lived entirely in the will of God.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
